“This is a precautionary measure to ensure that the correct protocol is implemented so that normal operations may continue, said Andre Oosthuizen, hospital manager. “All persons who have been in close contact with the confirmed case have been notified and are currently in self-quarantine. The hospital is working closely with the NICD and Department of Health to ensure that all patient and visitor safety measures are in place. Further details will be communicated soon,” he said. Oosthuizen can be contacted on 013 752 7576 or email at AndreO@Busamed.co.za. ALSO READ: NCID confirms first coronavirus case in Mpumalanga